# Gitignore Rules

Maintain clean repository hygiene.

## Never commit

Never commit:
- .env files
- API keys
- secrets
- credentials
- private certificates
- SSH keys
- database dumps
- local SQLite databases
- caches
- virtual environments
- node_modules
- OS-generated files

## Python

Ensure these are ignored when applicable:

__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/

## Environment files

.env
.env.*
!.env.example

## Node / React

node_modules/
dist/
build/
.cache/
coverage/

## Logs and temp

*.log
logs/
tmp/

## IDE / OS

.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

## Security

If secrets are detected:
- warn immediately
- recommend removing them from git history
- use .env and .env.example
- never include real secrets in generated code or docs